Package com.cafean.client.integrator

Class AbstractIntegrator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.integrator.AbstractIntegrator
  • public abstract class AbstractIntegrator
extends java.lang.Object
    The base class for an integrator object used to detect, disconnect, and re-connect, CrossReference instances in a given Category of components.

      • getCrossReferences

        public java.util.List<CrossReference> getCrossReferences​(AbstractComponent fromComp,
                                                         AbstractSubSystem subsys)
        Returns a list of the crossreferences from the given component that cross the boundary of the given AbstractSubSystem.

        The returned CrossReferences can be assumed to have sufficient data to be able to locate the components on either side of the reference by using the component's "Unique ID" as returned by AbstractComponent.getUniqueID().

        Returns:
        a List<CrossReference> of the cross references in the given component

        public boolean isCrossReference​(Connection connection,
